comments: Turner (IND) briefly grasps Adams' (OKC) shorts, but does not affect his ability to rebound. Lamb (IND) then makes marginal contact with Adams' right forearm as they both attempt to retrieve the ball.
Turner (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Ferguson's (OKC) path and does not deliver the contact.
After the shot is cleanly blocked, Adams (OKC) and Brogdon (IND) make incidental foot-to-foot contact with one another as they attempt to retrieve the ball.
Warren (IND) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Ferguson (OKC) makes marginal body contact with Brogdon (IND) that does not affect his SQBR at the end of the drive.
Paul (OKC) has his forearm collapsed against his body when he makes marginal contact to Warren's (IND) body on his play to the basket.
Paul (OKC) makes contact with Warren's (IND) left arm and subsequently pulls Warren's hand off of the ball.  The contact occurs prior to his upward shooting motion.
Warren (IND) cleanly strips the ball away from Paul (OKC) during rebounding.
Warren (IND) makes contact across Adams' (OKC) right forearm during rebounding, causing him to lose control of the ball.
Turner (IND) and Ferguson (OKC) engage and disengage off-ball without affecting the other's FOM.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Lamb (IND) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Gallinari (OKC) establishes his screening position in Brogdon's (IND) path when marginal contact is made.
Turner (IND) makes marginal body contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Ferguson (OKC) makes contact across Brogdon's (IND) right arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Warren (IND) makes marginal contact with Paul's (OKC) front during the drive and does not affect his SQBR.
Paul (OKC) makes contact with the ball and incidental contact with Warren's (IND) hand that is considered part of the ball during rebounding.
Turner (IND) and Adams (OKC) engage and disengage while rebounding.
Adams (OKC) makes marginal contact with Warren's (IND) right shoulder that does not affect his rebounding position.
Paul (OKC) commits the take foul on Warren (IND).
Brogdon (IND) briefly has his arm on Paul's (OKC) midsection, but slides it off without affecting his FOM.
Brogdon (IND) and Adams (OKC) engage and disengage without affecting the other's FOM.
